                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200112-100-off555 t18200112-100-crimeloc558"></join>. On the 6th of December, between five and six o'clock, I was at the door, and saw the prisoner come by - he was my <rs id="t18200112-100-deflabel559" type="occupation">journeyman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200112-100-defend1004 t18200112-100-deflabel559"></join>, but had not been at work that day - a bedstead was stolen from the shop soon after; he went to work next day. I told him I had lost a bedstead, and that he had been hanging about all day. I went with him after some bed furniture which he had lost. He took me to a woman in Pulteney-street, she said he had not got it. He then took me to the Cock, public-house - the landlord said he had brought a bedstead there, and two men sold it in Castle-street.</p>
               <p>
            
